Serves: 4-6Difficulty: Easy, 50 minutesIngredients:200g butternut or pumpkin, cubed200g sweet potato, cubed100g brussels sprouts, optionalOlive oil for drizzling4 sage leaves, chopped2.5ml ( tsp) ground cumin2.5ml ( tsp) ground corianderSalt1 large clove garlic, unpeeled250ml (1 cup) whole freekeh, cooked as per packet instructionsLemon herb dressing:A handful of parsley, finely chopped5 sage leaves, finely chopped80ml (1 cup) extra virgin olive oilJuice of 1 lemonSalt and pepper to tasteMethod:1) Preheat the oven to 200 C.2) Place the butternut, sweet potato and brussels sprouts on a baking sheet and drizzle with oil.3) Sprinkle with the sage leaves, cumin, coriander and salt. Add the clove of garlic to the pan and roast the veggies for about 20-30 minutes until cooked through and the edges start to caramelise. Give it a gentle stir at least once. Remove the brussels sprouts if they are cooked and browning too much.4) Set the veggies and clove of garlic aside.5) Make the dressing by combining all the ingredients.6) Squeeze the roasted garlic into the mix and whisk until combined.8) Toss the freekeh and roasted vegetables together.9) Dress and serve.